{{Class 3}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level 2.1 1.png|caption=The infamous picture of this sublevel taken upon entry. It shows the entrance to this sublevel where the photographer entered from.|align=center}}
<div style="border: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);padding: 15px;margin: 2em;">
== <Div style="text-align: center;text-shadow: 0 0 1px var(--theme-header-text-color);">Description</div> ==
{{Underline|649664}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level 2.1 2.png|caption=A connection of two corridors and one has a broken ceiling, which let bright sunlight through.|width=250px|align=right}}
[[Level 268.1]] is a sublevel connected to [[Level 268]], and resembles a decayed and brutally cramped residential complex where disorder and age dominate every corner. The structure is built from concrete, majority of it sections are painted in green colors that has begun to peel, flake, or fade away, which exposes dull grey surfaces beneath. The ceiling is unusually low, and positioned just above 5-4 feet, which presses down on individuals and contributes to the overall feeling of confinement.

The layout forms a dense and unorganized network of hallways and rooms that leads into one another without clear pattern. The interiors have house furnitures and household items, all of which appear rotten, broken, or covered in layers of dust. Objects are rarely positioned with almost any sense of order, and piled together in cluttered heaps or collapsed in corners, which creates the sense of abandonment. Bedrooms with beds and frames sag because of their weight, blankets are messy, and closets contain clusters of decayed clothes. Kitchens, on the other hand, contain stoves, refrigerators, and utensils are rusty and some fragmented into pieces.

{{Blurimage|file=Level 2.1 3.png|align=left|caption=A small kitchen room with a wide window.|width=250px}}
Unlike its parent level, this sublevel features windows. These reveal an outside environment that appears to be a narrow walkway lined by sheets of corroded metal fencing and overgrown plants beyond it. Along these paths are flowerpots filled with plants, some of them are withered away, and clotheslines run along with wet clothes swaying in air. Access to this outer area is through green-painted doors that are outlined with metal frames, and which connect the inside network of rooms to the outdoor passages. The sunlight constantly changes in strength; sometimes subtle and cool, and other times warmer and heavier. Its temperature fluctuates irregularly between 10°C to 25°C.

Although the majority sections of [[Level 268.1]] is defined by its harsh low ceilings, rare sections exist where the ceiling is unusually high. These spaces feel significantly different from the rest of the complex. The walls in these areas stretch several meters higher, although stay painted in the same patchy green paint and dust, usually streaked with water stains that run downward in trails.

Within these rooms built the high ceilings, the air behaves strangely. Temperature changes violently between freezing cold and oppressive heat without any rhythm from 0°C to 40°C. The violent changes leave condensation dripping from the walls one moment, and dry into a suffocating stillness the next. The instability of these spaces makes them feel volatile.
{{Blurimage|file=Level 2.1 4.png|align=right|caption=A cramped room with a bed that is almost the width of the room, a network hang over and blankets are messy.|width=250px}}
Individuals who had explored these areas describe seeing cryptic symbols, patterns, and fragmented texts written in their visions or on the upper walls or across the ceiling surface. The symbols never stay long enough to read or study and dissolve into nothingness if one attempts to focus too intently. Their presence suggests that the structure itself may be attempting to communicate in some forgotten or coded language.

In opposition to the densely cluttered rooms of the main complex, some rare sections of [[Level 268.1]] have less objects. These areas are characterized by bland concrete floors and walls. Furniture here is absent or reduced to isolated remnants: a single cracked chair, a lonely mattress collapsed in a corner, or an empty frame of a table. The emptiness of these rooms contributes to their unsettling quality. Where majority of the sublevel are filled with disorder and piles of belongings, these spaces feature nothing and strange silence.

In some hallways, the minimalism becomes extreme. Long passages with nothing but bland concrete, lined by vacant alcoves that suggest furniture was once present. In rarer cases, the walls show rectangular discolorations where shelves or cabinets might once have been placed. These areas induce strong feelings of the sublevel being affected by [[Phenomenon 15]], although it is unconfirmed due to common reports of individuals finding eachother.
</div>

<div style="border: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);padding: 15px;margin: 2em;">
== <Div style="text-align: center;text-shadow: 0 0 1px var(--theme-header-text-color);">Entities</div> ==
{{Underline|649664}}
Several documented entities are known and confirmed to linger [[Level 268.1]], which are [[Entity 8|Hounds]], [[Sanguine Festivus]], [[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]], [[Hydrolitis Plague]], and [[Spines]]. Although those entities are quite rare to encounter, caution must be taken due to the high chance of facing aggressive entities that are only seen in this sublevel.

{{Blurimage|file=Level 2.1 7.png|caption=The first ever image to depict this entity, taken for entity confirmation by the [[M.E.G.]]|align=center}}
=== <Div style="text-align: center;text-shadow: 0 0 1px var(--theme-header-text-color);">Tree Giant</div> ===
{{Underline|649664}}
'''Tree Giants''' are massive entities that inhabit the outdoor sections of [[Level 268.1]], most usually seen beyond the rusty metal boards and narrow pathways. They resemble pale, lifeless, and leafless trees with long trunks, but closer distance reveals their humanoid shapes. Their legs are disproportionately long and usually the first feature to be noticed, and stretch upward into a body that continues far above the surrounding metal boards.

The surface of a '''Tree Giant'''’s body is smooth and brownish white, and it is covered in subtle red veins. In certain areas on the entity, red and spiky protrusions jut outward. These features are only visible when the entity has not sensed prey. Once it has noticed movement nearby, the body seems to sloy change, and obscures these details under a pale surface, which makes it appear more like a simple dead tree.

'''Tree Giants''' stay almost motionless when no chosen prey is within a close range, which camouflages into the environment. They has an unnatural scent of freshly baked steak that moves across their surrounding space, which lures prey closer under the false hope of food nearby. Once approached, the entity reveals its predatory nature.

When attacking, a '''Tree Giant''' makes sudden use of its limbs, kicking or crouching its lower body forward to grab prey. Victims caught by these movements usually get ensnared upon the sharp spikes hidden along its surface. Once ensnared, bleeding begins to flow out of the body and the '''Tree Giant'''’s pale skin reveals its consumption process: countless almost microscopic pores open across its body, sucking in blood until the victim is drained.

The most reliable way to identify a '''Tree Giant''' is by its lack of leaf. While it may resemble a dead, pale tree, no branches ever sprout leaves, and the scent of cooked meat lingering unnaturally in the air is a strong sign of its presence.

{{Blurimage|file=Level 2.1 8.png|caption=The photographer's very last image, which shows a dark corner with the entity's silhouette and the glowing eye looking at the photographer just before attack.|align=center}}
=== <Div style="text-align: center;text-shadow: 0 0 1px var(--theme-header-text-color);">The Darkener</div> ===
{{Underline|649664}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level 2.1 6.png|align=left|caption=Near their territory, a hallway ending into a wall with a washing machine.|width=250px}}
'''The Darkener''' is a tall, and skeletal humanoid figure with no visible neck; its head merges directly with its upper torso. Its dark body is thin, and its limbs have unnaturally long claws that resemble zigzag-shaped bones. A single large eye is positioned in the center of its head, and several pointy tubes from its head. These tubes exhale a strong black fog that much more darkens cramped hallways and dark corners, which gives the '''Darkener''' cover and a way to mark its territory.

'''Darkeners''' are ambush predators that prefer extremely narrow and dark areas. They wait silently, usually press themselves into corners or hidden behind decayed furniture. Once within enough distance, the entity leaps forward with rapid speed. At the moment of attack, its eye releases a piercing beam of concentrated light directly into the victim’s vision, which causes severe temporary blindness. With its prey being blind, the '''Darkener''' uses its claws to tear, slash, and drag the body apart, usually plays with its victim's parts before eventually consuming it piece by piece.

The territories they inhabit are defined by noticeable features. Green paint on the walls is frequently absent in these areas, which leaves only flat concrete. Black fog obscure visibility in the air. Hints of past attacks, bloodstains, scraps of flesh, and the odor of rotten meat, are common indicators of their presence. Within the mist, a fleeting glimpse of their glowing eye is usually the only warning before the attack.

'''Darkeners''' are solitary and territorial, and rarely seen outside their chosen zones. When not actively hunting, they stay still, which their thin silhouettes can be easily mistaken for shadows or broken debris. This stillness with their ability to saturate an area with fog, makes them one of the most deceptive presences in [[Level 268.1]].
</div>

<div style="border: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);padding: 15px;margin: 2em;">
== <Div style="text-align: center;text-shadow: 0 0 1px var(--theme-header-text-color);">Human Habitations</div> ==
{{Underline|649664}}
[[Level 268.1]] does not support long-term habitation. Its cramped architecture, unstable conditions, and lack of resources make survival here unsustainable. For this reason, no outposts, bases, or communities have ever been established here.
</div>

<div style="border: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);padding: 15px;margin: 2em;">
== <Div style="text-align: center;text-shadow: 0 0 1px var(--theme-header-text-color);">Entrances & Exits</div> ==
{{Underline|649664}}

=== <Div style="text-align: center;text-shadow: 0 0 1px var(--theme-header-text-color);">Entrances</div> ===
{{Underline|649664}}
* Exploring a completely dark area within [[Level 268]], may lead to an area that is only illuminated by a ray of sunlight which is coming from a torn down door that directs here.
* Although this can be dangerous, breaking a severely cracked green-painted wall within [[Level 268]], with a hammer, or any weapon, can lead to this sublevel.
* Wandering extremely far enough into [[Level 268]], has been reported by some individuals to transition the level into [[Level 268.1]].

{{Blurimage|file=Level 2.1 5.png|caption=A low-quality image which shows the exit door that is covered by wet hanging clothes.|align=center}}
=== <Div style="text-align: center;text-shadow: 0 0 1px var(--theme-header-text-color);">Exits</div> ===
{{Underline|649664}}
* Going back through the door where one entered the sublevel from, obviously leads back to [[Level 268]]. Although commonly, the door may be sealed right after entry by a brick wall that appears new, as if something unseen intentionally built it in a blink of an eye.
* A strangely clean locked door with the number 269 displayed on it, can be unlocked by a [[Object 2|Level Key]] that has the same number, and which the door opens to [[Level 269]]. The [[Object 2|Level Key]] can be seen placed under piles of book, in the back of a closet, or in a drawer.
* A rusty exit grate door covered by wet hanging clothes in an area near a '''Darkener''' territory, exits back to [[Level 268]]. Finding this exit can be dangerous due to the danger of '''The Darkeners'''.
* Opening gray closets is reported by some individuals to open to [[Level 268]], but this method is still not confirmed, which can be unreliable.
</Div>
